# Privacy Policy for VScreen

**Last Updated: May 4, 2025**

## Introduction

Welcome to VScreen. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy explains our practices regarding data privacy as it relates to the use of our application.

## No Data Collection

**VScreen does not collect, store, or transmit any personal information or data.**

VScreen is designed as a simple utility tool that enables users to view connected displays or app windows in a separate window. The application:

- Does not request or require user accounts
- Does not collect personal information
- Does not use cookies or tracking technologies
- Does not access your contacts, photos, or other personal data
- Does not connect to any servers or external services
- Does not contain in-app purchases or advertisements
- Does not transmit any information over the internet

## Local Operation Only

VScreen operates entirely on your local device. All processes and functionality occur locally on your computer without any data being sent to external servers.

## Third-Party Services

VScreen does not integrate with or utilize any third-party services, analytics tools, or APIs that would collect information about you or your usage of the application.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy.

We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

## Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:

- By creating an issue on our GitHub repository: [https://github.com/adaskar/VScreen](https://github.com/adaskar/VScreen)

## Consent

By using VScreen, you consent to our Privacy Policy.

---

This policy is effective as of the date listed at the top of this document.
